    <!-- NX-416 -->
    <h2 id="nx-416">Alfa Laval NX 416 B-31 Decanter Centrifuge</h2>

    <p>
      The Alfa Laval NX 416 Decanter is a two-phase decanter centrifuge for the 2-phase separation of wastewater, municipal sludge thickening, crude oil tank bottom recovery, <a href="/wvo-centrifuge-separator/">UCO desludging</a>, etc. With a 20 HP Motor, the NX 416 decanter centrifuge has a bowl RPM of 4,000 and can process 40 GPM of UCO @ 180 F.
    </p>

    <p>
      The NX 416 features a longer 46-inch bowl compared to the NX 314's 34-inch bowl, providing a higher Area Equivalent (AE) of 1,170 versus 780 for the NX 314. This increased separation area allows the NX 416 to handle higher flow rates and achieve better clarification on difficult-to-separate feed streams. The more powerful 15 HP drive motor and larger processing capacity make the NX 416 the preferred choice for higher-volume operations such as used cooking oil recycling facilities and large-scale <a href="/industrial-wastewater-treatment-centrifuge/">industrial wastewater treatment</a> plants.
    </p>

