    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What is the capacity of the Alfa Laval NX 314 decanter centrifuge?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The Alfa Laval NX 314 decanter centrifuge has a rated capacity of 25 GPM on hemp ethanol slurry. It is driven by a 10 HP motor with a bowl speed of 4,000 RPM, generating 3,157 Gs of centrifugal force for effective two-phase solid/liquid separation. Actual throughput varies depending on the specific application, feed solids concentration, and required separation efficiency.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What applications is the NX 314 decanter used for?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The NX 314 decanter is used for hemp solvent extraction, ethanol extraction, waste oil de-sludging, crude oil tank bottom sludge recovery, municipal wastewater treatment, pyrolysis sludge separation, liquid humus fertilizer processing, and sludge thickening and dewatering. Its versatile design and adjustable auger differential speed make it adaptable to a wide variety of industrial separation tasks.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What is the difference between the NX 314, AVNX 414, and NX 416 decanters?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The NX 314 is a two-phase decanter with a 10 HP motor and 34-inch bowl length, ideal for mid-range applications at 25 GPM. The AVNX 414 is a three-phase decanter with a 15 HP motor for industrial wastewater, crude oil slop, and WVO desludging. The NX 416 is a larger two-phase decanter with a 20 HP motor, 46-inch bowl, and AE of 1,170, capable of processing 40 GPM of UCO at 180°F.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Can the NX 314 be supplied as a modular packaged unit?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Yes, the Alfa Laval NX-314 decanter can be supplied as a complete modular packaged unit. This plug-and-play system includes all ancillary equipment for standalone operation: a sludge conveyor, clean fluid tank with transfer pump, feed pump, and electric pre-heater. Dolphin Centrifuge also builds custom sunflower oil desludging modules with stainless steel collection tanks.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What type of conveyor protection does the NX 314 decanter have?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The Alfa Laval NX 314 decanter features carbide tile or tungsten carbide hard-surfacing on the conveyor (auger) for protection against abrasive wear. This extends service life in demanding applications such as sludge dewatering, tank bottom recovery, and paint sludge handling. Contact <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Dolphin Centrifuge</a> to discuss your specific application requirements.</p>
      </details>
    </div>

